article.headline: Long Beach St. 81, Pacific 80
article.story: LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Casper Ware's two free throws with 13.4 seconds left in the second overtime gave Long Beach State a 81-80 victory over Pacific Saturday. Michael Kirby's last second shot went off the back rim and Stephan Gilling rebounded the ball to secure the win for the 49ers. The 49ers (12-10, 6-4 Big West Conference) increased their first-place conference lead to one game over idle Cal State Northridge. It marked only the fourth time in the last 13 games that Long Beach State has defeated Pacific (12-9, 5-5). Long Beach State outscored the Tigers 16-15 in the overtime periods. Ware missed a 15 footer with 1 second left in the first OT forcing a second overtime period. Long Beach State had a chance to win in the first OT but Gilling's misfired on a 3-point attempt at the buzzer in regulation sending the game into overtime.
